Another major achievement is the development of more robust and reliable quantum error correction codes, such as the surface code and the Gottesman-Kitaev-Preskill (GKP) code, which have improved the fidelity of quantum computations (Fowler et al., 2012; Gottesman et al., 2001). Furthermore, there has been significant progress in the development of quantum algorithms, including the Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm (QAOA) and the Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE), which have shown promising results for solving complex optimization problems and simulating many-body systems (Farhi et al., 2014; Peruzzo et al., 2014). Gottesman, D., Kitaev, A., & Preskill, J. (2001). Encoding a qubit in an oscillator. Physical Review A, 64(1), 012310.

Peruzzo, A., McClean, J., Shadbolt, P., Yung, M.-H., Zhou, X.-Q., Campbell, P. L., ... & O'Brien, J. L. (2014). A variational eigenvalue solver for molecular systems. Physical Review Letters, 113(9), 090502.
